Standard and Poor's Corp said itdowngraded Canada's Province of Saskatchewan. The actionaffects the equivalent of 1.68 billion U.S. dlrs of debt.    S and P lowered the province's long-term debt to AA-minusfrom AA.    The rating agency said the action reflected a substantialincrease in Saskatchewan's budget deficit for fiscal 1987 andprospects for greater tax-supported debt in the medium term.    S and P pointed out that the outlook for future revenuegrowth is constrained by general weakness in the province'scommodity-based economy because of low prices. Reuter&#3;